    <string name="profile_faq_screen_title">Help &amp; FAQ</string>
    <string name="profile_faq_header_title">Frequently asked questions</string>
    <string name="profile_faq_header_subtitle">Quick answers about downloads, playback, and data differences.</string>
    <string name="profile_faq_q1_title">Why is there no download everything button?</string>
    <string name="profile_faq_q1_body">Mass downloads heavily load content hosts and can slow access for everyone. You
        can still download files post by post.
    </string>
    <string name="profile_faq_q2_title">Does the app have its own video player?</string>
    <string name="profile_faq_q2_body">Not yet. For stable playback, open videos in a dedicated player like VLC or your
        preferred app.
    </string>
    <string name="profile_faq_q3_title">How do I listen to audio files?</string>
    <string name="profile_faq_q3_body">For online audio playback, use VLC. The app will open the media stream in VLC or
        another compatible external player.
    </string>
    <string name="profile_faq_q4_title">The website and app show different data. What should I do?</string>
    <string name="profile_faq_q4_body">Please open an issue and include an example link. This helps reproduce the
        mismatch and fix it faster.
    </string>
    <string name="profile_faq_q5_title">I get a 500 error. Is it my fault?</string>
    <string name="profile_faq_q5_body">No. HTTP 500 means an internal server error. Usually this is a temporary
        server-side issue, so try again later.
    </string>
    <string name="profile_faq_q6_title">Why do video previews sometimes not load?</string>
    <string name="profile_faq_q6_body">The preview server requests the original video, and sometimes that file is
        corrupted or temporarily unavailable. When that happens, the preview may fail to load.
    </string>
    <string name="profile_faq_q7_title">If profile requests fail with 500/400 errors</string>
    <string name="profile_faq_q7_body">Try disabling the tabs that trigger errors in Settings.</string>

